---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---
<BaseLayout title="Erodian Encyclopedia" description="The collected knowledge of the Erodian Atlasing Society — continents, gods, factions, history, and more.">

  <div class="enc-homepage">

    <div class="enc-preface">
      <em>Compiled and maintained by the <strong>Erodian Atlasing Society</strong></em>
      <blockquote>
        My associates and I have been compiling histories of this ancient land for as long as the Fowlmen have walked Siroth.
        Korlornium is quite a fascinating continent full of geopolitical conflict, natural wonders, and debauchery.
        Due to the instability over the past 2000 years, information is difficult to come by for this region.
        Thereby you may notice gaps in our manuscripts — but be advised we will update this text as new information
        and historical accounts come to light. We hope you enjoy reading the collected text and may immerse yourself
        in the rich and mysterious land which many of the authors of this text call home.
      </blockquote>
    </div>

    <div class="enc-nav-cards">
      <a href={`${base}/static/map/`} class="map-card">
        <div class="map-card-title">&#10022; Map of Korlornium &#10022;</div>
        <div class="map-card-sub">An interactive atlas — zoom, explore, and click any location</div>
      </a>
      <a href={`${base}/static/calendar/`} class="map-card">
        <div class="map-card-title">&#10022; Erodian Calendar &#10022;</div>
        <div class="map-card-sub">Track the in-world date, moons, and seasons of Erodas</div>
      </a>
      <a href={`${base}/static/vote/`} class="map-card map-card--vote">
        <div class="map-card-title">&#10022; Vote: Next Adventure &#10022;</div>
        <div class="map-card-sub">Cast your voice — regions, vibes, and themes for the next campaign</div>
      </a>
    </div>

    <hr />

    <h2>The Known World of Erodas</h2>

    <p>
      <a href={`${base}/world-(erodas)/erodas`}>Erodas</a> is a living world — two moons overhead, four seasons,
      and a history older than memory. Below are the continents currently charted by the Atlasing Society.
      Some are well-documented; others remain at the edge of legend.
    </p>

    <div class="continent-grid">

      <div class="continent-card">
        <h3><a href={`${base}/world-(erodas)/korlornium`}>Korlornium</a></h3>
        <em>A small, isolated continent — the heart of the campaign</em>
        <p>
          A land of theological strife, diverse ecology, and unique geological phenomena.
          Divided by <a href={`${base}/world-(erodas)/korlornium/the-scar`}>The Scar</a>, the western forests of
          <a href={`${base}/world-(erodas)/korlornium/caldrith`}>Caldrith</a> are home to wealthy cities and complex factions,
          while the arid eastern expanse of <a href={`${base}/world-(erodas)/korlornium/siroth`}>Siroth</a> is harsh,
          conservative, and deep with history. Two thousand years since the Great Wave, the scars of catastrophe still shape its people.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="continent-card">
        <h3><a href={`${base}/world-(erodas)/dracofold`}>Dracofold</a></h3>
        <em>Volcanic continent of draconic origin — ruled by the dragon queen</em>
        <p>
          The air above Dracofold smells of sulfur and hot stone. Tiamat's rule is absolute here — chromatic dragons
          serve as her lieutenants, and humanoid populations survive under their shadow. Rogue dragons exiled from her
          court have spread across Erodas, settling in remote regions and establishing their own smaller tyrannies.
          At the continent's molten heart lies the <strong>Cradle of Scales</strong>, where all dragonkind is said to have been born.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="continent-card">
        <h3><a href={`${base}/world-(erodas)/goghdor`}>Goghdor</a></h3>
        <em>A towering fjord — closer to the heavens than anywhere else on Erodas</em>
        <p>
          Known across Erodas as <strong>The Reach</strong>, Goghdor is not a continent in the traditional sense —
          it is a single colossal rock rising from the ocean, its peaks so high that those who live at the summit exist
          above the clouds. Home to the <strong>Star Touched</strong>, Aasimar of elven and dwarven blood whose culture
          is built entirely around the celestial.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="continent-card">
        <h3><a href={`${base}/world-(erodas)/seivara`}>Seivara</a></h3>
        <em>Ancient jungle continent — more legend than fact to most of Korlornium</em>
        <p>
          Sailors who have seen its coastline describe a wall of green so dense the sea appears to simply end at a forest.
          Seivara has no kings, no churches, and no organized religion. Authority here belongs to the <strong>Ara</strong> —
          ancient nature spirits that inhabit every river, grove, and tidal pool.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <hr />

    <h2>Explore the Encyclopedia</h2>

    <h3>Peoples &amp; Powers</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong><a href={`${base}/factions`}>Factions</a></strong> — Guilds, gangs, dynasties, and secret societies</li>
      <li><strong><a href={`${base}/gods-and-higher-powers`}>Gods and Higher Powers</a></strong> — The divine forces worshipped and feared across Erodas</li>
      <li><strong><a href={`${base}/species`}>Species</a></strong> — The peoples and creatures who call Erodas home</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>The World Beyond</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong><a href={`${base}/history`}>History</a></strong> — Timelines, calendars, and the ages that shaped the present</li>
      <li><strong><a href={`${base}/ecology`}>Ecology</a></strong> — Flora, fauna, and the natural phenomena of Erodas</li>
      <li><strong><a href={`${base}/planes`}>Planes</a></strong> — The realms of existence beyond the material world</li>
      <li><strong><a href={`${base}/celestial-bodies`}>Celestial Bodies</a></strong> — The moons and stars of Erodas</li>
    </ul>

  </div>

</BaseLayout>
